  "riddle": "1. In the small French commune where the river flows, look for its precise spot in the geographic realm; the coordinates hold your first clue.\n\n2. Ascend from the ground to discover how high this charming place reaches above sea level.\n\n3. Libraries stand as portals to knowledge; how many of these establishments grace the vicinity of your last finding?\n\n4. Take the elevation you uncovered and sum it with the count of nearby libraries — what new number unfolds before you?\n\n5. Seek the location of a renowned temple depicted in a visual from a nearby region. Where does this sacred structure reside?\n\n6. In what way does the name of that holy place echo through time? Count the vowels within it — a transformation awaits.\n\n7. A linguistic feature once flourished here; can you recall the years when Italian script ruled the writing, during a brief occupation?\n\n8. Turning your gaze to the nation, inquire about the total number of inhabitants who call France home.\n\n9. A culinary delight emerged from a certain origin; to which port does this flavor trace its roots?\n\n10. The people thrive within and beyond regions — what is the population count of the land you’ve discovered thus far?\n\n11. Measure the expanse of the nation; how many square kilometers encompass the land of these delicious delicacies?\n\n12. Now, combine the count of inhabitants with the area they reside in — what total do you unearth?\n\n13. Travel to a part of the United States known for its picturesque towns. What is the height of the ground there above sea level?\n\n14. Reflect on the digits of that elevation; what is the digital root of the sum that stays singular?\n\n15. In the realm of herbs, identify the variety most favored in kitchens across the globe — who is this aromatic wonder?\n\n16. Finally, calculate the absolute difference between the population you discovered and the digit from your earlier height inquiry, then take that result modulo 10 to reveal your final treasure.",
